# Webhook config 

A webhook should be provided following the format below.
We'll use the endpoint `/config` prefixed by your `BASE_URL` to fetch the configuration.

```json
{
  "config": {
    "fields": [
      {
        "id": "type",
        "label": "Test",
        "placeholder": "Select test",
        "type": "select",
        "options": [
          { "id": 1, "label": "Algorithm test" },
          { "id": 2, "label": "Data structure test" },
          { "id": 3, "label": "Project" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "threshold",
        "label": "Threshold",
        "placeholder": "Minimum score to pass",
        "type": "number",
        "step": 5,
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Attributes

Attribute        | Type    | Description
-----------------|---------|------------
config           | object  | Top-level object
fields           | array   | List of possible fields

### Field objects

Field objects follow the HTML form standard in regards to types, possible options, labels and placeholders.
For example, __step__, __min__ and __max__ may be provided for the __"number"__ type and an __options__ array
may be provided for the __"select"__ type.

Attribute        | Type    | Description
-----------------|---------|------------
id               | string  | Identifier for this field 
label            | string  | Human readable label
placeholder      | string  | Form placeholder
type             | string  | Type of form element


